Merge pull request #10 from octurite/dev/octurite/tcpmux-droppriv-fix

CVE-2013-4342: xinetd ignores user and group directives for TCPMUX services

Merge pull request #4 from ltworf/debug_udpint

- Can compile with DEBUG_UDPINT enabled.

Merge pull request #3 from ltworf/documentation_fixes

Documentation fixes

CVE-2013-4342: xinetd: ignores user and group directives for TCPMUX services

Originally reported to Debian in 2005 <http://bugs.debian.org/cgi-bin/bugreport.cgi?bug=324678> and rediscovered <https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1006100>, xinetd would execute TCPMUX services without dropping privilege to match the service configuration allowing the service to run with same privilege as the xinetd process (root).

- Can compile with DEBUG_UDPINT enabled.

Patch from #873194 on launchpad
https://bugs.launchpad.net/ubuntu/+source/xinetd/+bug/873194

Adds escapes to manpages
More realistic examples paths

Fix man installation path

section 5 is for File formats and conventions
The Documentation fixes patch from the debian package.

Merge pull request #2 from boocz3ch/master

Various small fixes
sconf.c: fix possible memleak
connection.c: fix possible close() call with fd == -1
int.c: fix possible uninitialized value call when socket family detection fails
Fix typo in xinetd.conf manpage
service.c: avoid dereferencing NULL pointer

Merge pull request #1 from boocz3ch/master

multiple small fixes
inet.c: avoid using pointer after free
tcpint.c: fix memleak
connection.c: fix pointer dereference before NULL check
confparse.c: fix wrong function name in log message
parse.c: fix wrong function name in log message
Fix gcc warnings about using register storage variable in va_start
Update attribution, and bump version number
Merge patch from RedHat regarding CVE-2012-0862
Add a fix to prevent crashing when a service hits its log limit.
Fix compile warning in itox.c.

Merge the Fedora patch for int->ssize_t.
	Patch xinetd-2.3.14-ssize_t.patch r1.1
	Some modifications to this patch were necessary.
Change compiler flags, -Wconversion generates excessive and
	unnecessary warnings with gcc, particularly all
	cases of ntohs(uint16_t).
	http://gcc.gnu.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=6614
	Additionally add -Wno-unused to prevent unnecessary
	warnings regarding unused function parameters when
	the function is a callback conforming to a standard
	interface.
Change version number to 2.3.15devel, indicating an interim
	developmental source snapshot.

Merge the Fedora patch to add labeled networking.
	Patch xinetd-2.3.14-label.patch r1.4.
Merge the Fedora patch to fix getpeercon() for labeled networking
	in MLS environments.
	Patch xinetd-2.3.14-contextconf.patch r1.1
Merge the Fedora patch to turn off libwrap processing on tcp rpc services. Patch xinetd-2.3.12-tcp_rpc.patch.

If the address we're binding to is a multicast address, perform the
multicast group join.
Fix a problem with env.c when passing passenv environment variables.
